Beijing market supervision department to carry out comprehensive law enforcement before the festival commodity prices are basically stable
Beijing, September 27 (Reporter Du Yan) In order to strengthen the pre-holiday market supervision and law enforcement, the Beijing Municipal Bureau of Market Supervision inspected more than 2,000 households of various business entities on the eve of the National Day.
The inspection shows that the supply of daily necessities such as grain and oil, meat, fruits, vegetables, and egg milk sold in the market is sufficient, the commodity price is basically stable, no serious violations have been found, and the market business order is generally stable.
Today, the reporter learned from the Beijing Municipal Bureau of Market Supervision that the Bureau carried out the "comprehensive law enforcement inspection day" activities in the city, focusing on price, industrial and commercial, quality supervision, food and medicine, commerce and other factors, all aspects of law enforcement inspection in key areas and key areas, and comprehensively standardized the market business order.
According to reports, the Beijing Municipal Bureau of Market Supervision price, industry and commerce, quality supervision, food and medicine, commerce and other five law enforcement teams coordinated, closely cooperated, led by the heads of various law enforcement agencies, grouped on the random selection of some business entities for joint law enforcement inspection.
During the inspection, law enforcement officials focused on the inspection of price behavior, advertising, food safety, measurement standards, production safety systems and so on.
The market supervision bureaus of each district also organized joint law enforcement inspections, a total of more than 1,600 law enforcement personnel, inspection of all kinds of business entities more than 2000 households, the inspection shows that the market sales of grain and oil, meat, fruits, vegetables, egg milk and other necessities of life supply is sufficient, commodity prices are basically stable, operators can abide by the law, did not find serious violations of the law, the market business order is generally stable.
The Beijing Municipal Bureau of Market Supervision said that during the National Day, emergency duty will be strengthened, continuous inspection and inspection of the market, and all kinds of market supervision issues will be dealt with quickly in accordance with the law, and the business violations reflected by the public will be dealt with seriously in accordance with the law, so as to effectively safeguard the legitimate rights and interests of consumers.
Confucius Institute of the Royal Cambodian Academy of Sciences "China in My Heart" Chinese Essay Contest Announced
The Chinese essay contest "China in My Heart" with the theme of the 70th anniversary of New China was announced and held at the Confucius Institute of the Royal Cambodian Academy of Sciences on the 26th.
The diplomats of the Chinese Embassy in Cambodia, Zhongxingfa, representatives of the Cambodian-Chinese Council, and Wei Siyu, President of the Jiangxi Chamber of Commerce in Cambodia, presented the award to the awardees.
According to the Chinese director of the Confucius Institute of the Royal Cambodian Academy of Sciences, the competition lasted for two months, and the participants were Cambodian primary school students, secondary school students (including special students) and university students (including social personnel).
The Chinese Embassy in Cambodia, diplomat Zhongxingfa, issued the award certificate to Lin Weicai, the first prize winner of the university group, and Guo Lina, the first prize winner of the primary and secondary school group.
Chakqing said that the entries were carried out separately according to the university group and the primary and secondary school groups, and invited the Cambodian senior Chinese experts to the judging committee, and through the initial evaluation, review and final evaluation, the final selection of the first prize of the university group, 2 second prizes, 3 third prizes, 10 excellent awards; 1 first prize in primary and secondary school, 5 second prizes, 10 third prizes, and 20 excellent awards.
Lin Weicai, the first prize winner of the university group, said that learning Chinese has been 15 years and has had a huge impact on himself.
Through the essay contest, it is to describe the well-being brought to Cambodia under the "Belt and Road" and the traditional friendship between China and Cambodia, and it is hoped that the younger generation will continue to add to the China-Cambodia friendship.
The guests and the winners.
Guo Lina, the first prize winner of the primary and secondary school group, said that as an overseas Chinese, she has the opportunity to express the emotion of "China in the heart" through the national language of the motherland and win the award, which has different excitement.
The organizers said that through the competition, not only created a positive atmosphere in China-Cambodia relations, but also attracted more and more Cambodian students to learn Chinese and study in China.
The United Nations International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) released a report on the 26th that Iran has begun to use advanced centrifuges to accelerate the production of enriched uranium, in further violation of the 2015 nuclear agreement with the world's major powers.
According to the IAEA report, advanced centrifuges at Iran's Natanz Nuclear Facility are "accumulating or ready to accumulate enriched uranium."
Since U.S. President Donald Trump pulled out of the nuclear deal last May and imposed sanctions on Iran, Iran is gradually violating the limits of the 2015 nuclear deal with major powers.
The agreement stipulates that Iran can only use the first generation of IR-1 centrifuges to refine uranium.
Other signatories to the deal, Britain, China, France, Germany and Russia, have been trying to salvage the deal, but Tehran has repeatedly accused Europe of not doing enough.
According to the Japanese Kyodo News Agency, on the afternoon of the 25th local time, Japanese Foreign Minister Motegi Minchong held talks with Russian Foreign Minister Lavrov in New York, the country where he visited the United States, and confirmed that he would promote the conclusion and negotiation of a peace treaty including the four northern islands (the disputed islands of Japan and Russia, the Japanese name the "Northern Islands", the "Southern Kuril Islands") territorial issues, and the development of bilateral relations in a wide range of political and economic fields.
This is the first consultation with Russia since Motegi took office as foreign minister and as the head of the peace treaty conclusion negotiations.
Motegi told the Russian side that "including the promotion of common economic activities (in the four northern islands), we hope to effectively carry out consultations."
According to the Japanese government, the talks did not hold detailed discussions on the territorial issue.
At the Japan-Russia summit in December 2018, the two foreign ministers were confirmed as heads of the two countries to accelerate negotiations.
At the talks, the foreign ministers of the two countries welcomed the progress of consultations on common economic activities in the fields of tourism and waste disposal.
Motegi expressed his expectation for the pilot tourism business scheduled for October: "I hope to successfully implement it and promote the next step."
In addition, the talks also confirmed that Lavrov will cooperate with the G20 foreign ministers' meeting in Nagoya in November.
Tuioneta was elected as the new Prime Minister of Tonga.
The Parliament of the South Pacific island nation of Tonga elected the current Minister of Finance and National Planning, Pohiva Tuionetoa, as Tonga's new prime minister, to replace former Prime Minister Akilisi Pohiva, who died of illness earlier this month.
According to the website of Tonga's main media, MAMANGI, the Tongan Parliament is unicameral and consists of 26 members.
In the parliamentary vote on the same day, Tuionetoa won 23 votes, defeating rival Deputy Prime Minister and Minister of Infrastructure and Tourism Semisi Sika and was elected.
Tonga is a constitutional monarchy with a system of separation of powers, both administrative, legislative and judicial.
Tuioneta was still to be appointed by the king.
The next Tongan parliamentary elections will be held in 2021.
