Garbage classification education first into Jilin kindergarten environmental protection concept from the doll
On the 27th, a kindergarten in Jilin City, Jilin Province, carried out a garbage classification education class to teach young children to distinguish recyclable garbage and other types of garbage.
It is reported that this is the first time that garbage classification has entered the local early childhood education classroom.
Recently, Jilin Province, nine departments jointly issued the Jilin Province to promote the classification and treatment of municipal domestic waste work plan.
In 2019, on the basis of the pilot project of compulsory classification of domestic waste in Changchun, the province decided to carry out the classification of domestic waste in prefecture-level cities.
Jilin City is one of them.
We hope that through this event, we can realize the effect of driving families with young children and kindergartens to drive society, and advocate the concept of environmental protection.
Liu Lijuan, executive director of the International Kindergarten, who held the event, said.
On the same day, the director read the environmental protection proposal, hoping that the classification of garbage will start from the children.
After the children performed the "Low-Carbon Beibei" dance, they started a small game of garbage classification.
The instructor also issued “recyclable” and “other garbage” labels, suggesting that children stick to the trash and record small videos when they get home.
Liu Lijuan introduced that the kindergarten has always advocated the concept of low-carbon and green environmental protection, and regularly opened environmental protection lecture halls.
The garbage drop-off office in the park has also set up a taxable garbage can, which is marked with the placement category.
Teachers teach children what recyclable garbage 苍雁
According to preliminary statistics, the amount of urban domestic waste generated in Jilin Province in 2018 was about 5,465,2 million tons, all of which entered the domestic waste disposal site for processing.
Among them, the sanitary landfill was 3,292,900 tons, incineration of 2.0923 million tons, and 80,100 tons of comprehensive utilization processes were taken.
After years of efforts, all cities and counties in the province have the ability to treat domestic waste harmlessly.
In the work plan of Jilin Province to promote the classification and disposal of prefecture-level urban domestic waste, it is explicitly required to carry out in-depth activities such as garbage classification into schools, teaching materials, and into the classroom, and strengthen the interaction between students and parents by creating garbage classification songs, songs, comics, micro-videos and other works, so as to achieve the effect of "teaching a child, influencing a family, driving a community, and cultivating a new generation".
