Chirac's death, political legacy persists
On the 26th local time, former French President Jacques Chirac died suddenly at the age of 86.
At a time when the world is in the midst of a century of unprecedented change, the many political legacies left by this French politician during his time in power are still worthy of our praise.
Chirac served as president of France for 12 years in a very humiliating manner.
He inherited the diplomatic spirit of Gaullism's independence and independence, but also firmly supported European integration, and was a representative of the pursuit of the "European dream".
At the same time, he also vigorously advocates multi-polarization and multilateralism in the world, and is a politician with strategic vision.
That is why the French media described him as "France's outstanding representative on the world stage".
One of Chirac’s relishing political decisions was his opposition to the US-led war in Iraq.
Under his leadership, France and Germany stood up to the pressure of the United States and were at the forefront of the anti-war.
A year after the war broke out, he predicted that the war in Iraq would lead to increased terrorist activity and made the world more dangerous.
Later it turned out that Chirac’s warning was correct.
At a time when European integration is in a trance and the unilateralism of the United States is becoming more and more prominent, Chirac is undoubtedly of great inspiration for strategic thinking and choice in international politics and global affairs.
Chirac is also a French politician who makes the Chinese feel familiar and affectionate.
He is one of the advocates and creators of the "Golden Decade" of Sino-French relations, and after being elected as the French president for the first time in 1995, he promoted the rapid development of Sino-French relations with a strategic vision of politicians.
In 2004, China and France established a comprehensive strategic partnership, and bilateral exchanges between China and France entered a new stage.
During the Jacques administration, bilateral trade between China and France grew rapidly, and the cooperation between the two countries in various fields such as aviation, nuclear energy and railway transportation has made breakthrough progress.
The Chinese-French Year of Culture initiated by Chirac has created a new model of cultural exchange in the history of China and France.
Chirac’s lifelong love of Chinese culture was particularly impressive.
It is understood that his Chinese diplomat introduced that Chirac can carry some poems of Li Bai and Du Fu, and even accurately judge the historical era of Chinese bronzes.
"Not looking at the pyramids is not really to go to Egypt, and not to see Qin Jun really to China" - this golden sentence comes from Chirac.
In an interview with Xinhua News Agency, Chirac said: "The West has concerns about China's political and social development, the ecological problems caused by China's economic growth, and China's political status in the international arena.
I have full confidence in China.
I think China is a country with a long history of civilization, and its experience is enough to help it build the concept and values of harmonious development and shoulder its responsibilities on the world stage for a long time.”
I also believe that China's rejuvenation will bring new creative vitality to the world culture and enrich the world culture.
The Szs have gone, but Chirac left the world with a legacy and revelation will live on.
