Members of the Legislative Council of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region signed a petition against the US Hong Kong-related bill
Some formed members of the Legislative Council of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region issued a joint statement on the 27th, expressing strong opposition to the passage of the "Hong Kong Human Rights and Democracy Act of 2019" by the Foreign Affairs Committees of the Senate and the House of Representatives of the United States Congress.
The statement, signed by 40 formed councillors, said that the rights enjoyed by Hong Kong are vested in the Basic Law of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region, including maintaining the status of free trade port and separate customs territory, signing and implementing bilateral and multilateral agreements in the name of "Hong Kong, China" in different fields such as economy, finance, shipping, trade, trade, trade, tourism, culture and sports, and signing and implementing bilateral and multilateral agreements in the name of "Hong Kong, China".
These rights are not granted by any foreign government or legislature.
Hong Kong has always strictly adhered to international agreements, international rules, laws and business ethics, trade with different countries and regions, and participated in many relevant areas of cooperation.
The statement said that the move by the Foreign Affairs Committee of the House and Senate of the United States to pass the relevant bill is not necessary, but in response to the call of its agents, as a means of crudely interfering in Hong Kong's internal affairs and seeking political leverage for their agents in Hong Kong.
Members of the establishment deeply regretd the move by the United States Congress and strongly opposed it.
Hong Kong is an important trading partner of the United States and the largest source of trade surplus.
Hong Kong's excellent rule of law, fair and free business environment, and a clean society make it a good place for American businessmen to do business.
If the United States passes this bill, in addition to attacking the interests of Hong Kong and the United States itself, it will make Sino-US relations worse, without any benefit and harm to others.
The statement said that Hong Kong will, as always, unswervingly implement the "one country, two systems" policy, continue to enjoy the rights granted by the Basic Law, and earnestly fulfill its obligations.
Whether in the past, present or future, Hong Kong will continue to make its due contribution to the international community and international trade.
According to the European Times on the 26th, the two houses of the French parliament will discuss immigration reform next week.
French President Emmanuel Macron recently claimed that France cannot “accept everyone,” but at the same time strives to “accept properly.”
Macron is trying to find a compromise route on immigration, slowing the impact of the upcoming debate.
Recently, Macron said in an interview during the general debate of the United Nations General Assembly in New York that he hoped to have a real "two-pronged" solution on immigration policy to find a balance between humanitarian and efficiency.
Macron said: "If France wants to be able to accept (immigration) properly, it will not be able to accept everyone."
Macron listed four priorities for immigration policy: granting asylum status to refugees in need of protection as soon as possible; more efficient promotion of integration of migrants; receiving and protecting all migrants entering French territory; and more efficient resettlement of people who enter France illegally and who are not suitable forstaying.
Whether illegal immigrants should be protected by the National Medical Assistance (AME) system is the most discussed topic.
Macron said he hoped to “assess” the system, but would not lift it, but would limit it.
After Macron's remarks, Le Pen, the leader of the far-right National Alliance, tweeted that Macron's statement was "empty talk".
Senate President Josh Lascher, a member of the right-wing Republican Party, also said that immigration policy should be discussed in a "mitative" but "realistic" way, indirectly criticizing Macron.
Varau, a member of parliament for the left-wing Socialist Party, said France should "accept more and better" on immigration, and criticized Macron for "manipulating" the issue.
The new version of the Asylum and Immigration Act, which has been in place for a year, has led to disagreements within the ruling party but has not been able to appease right-wing opposition parties.
In the next 2022 election, the topic of immigration policy will once again be the focus of attacks on the far right, and Macron needs to make a difference on this issue, but he will also risk angering the left wing inside the ruling party.
The lower chamber of the French National Assembly will debate immigration policy on September 30, and the Senate will debate it on October 2.
There are signs that China's A-shares are ushering in a "repurchase tide", and many listed companies have come up with "real money and silver" to buy back the company's shares.
According to the statistics of financial data service provider Oriental Wealth, as of the 27th, the total amount of repurchases of A-share listed companies in 2019 has exceeded 100 billion yuan (RMB, the same below), far exceeding the data of the same period in previous years, setting a record high in the amount of A-share stock repurchase funds.
In this regard, Xu Yang, chairman of Shanghai Mei Kerong Information Consulting Co., Ltd., said that the overall valuation of the A-share market this year is low, and the repurchase of shares at a relatively low price is conducive to listed companies to improve the efficiency of the use of funds, and also reflects the willingness of listed companies to actively manage market value and abundant cash flow, which is conducive to boosting investor confidence.
In addition, the continuous improvement of the share repurchase system has also promoted listed companies to actively carry out share repurchases.
For example, at the beginning of this year, the Shanghai Stock Exchange and the Shenzhen Stock Exchange issued the implementation rules for the repurchase of shares of listed companies, providing detailed share repurchase norms and guidelines for listed companies.
According to media statistics, since this year, listed companies that have implemented the repurchase plan have been mainly concentrated in the infrastructure industry, the real estate industry, the information technology industry and the electronic equipment manufacturing industry.
In addition, from the perspective of the amount of repurchase payments, six listed companies have repurchased more than 1 billion yuan this year.
Among them, the first is Yili shares, whose repurchase amount is more than 5 billion yuan.
What impact will the stock buyback of listed companies have on the market?
Zhao Xijun, vice president of the School of Finance and Finance of Renmin University of China, said in an interview with China News Agency that on the one hand, the repurchase shows that listed companies have strong economic strength and better financial situation, and has the ability to maintain stable stock prices and give investors confidence; on the other hand, it also shows that listed companies and their controlling shareholders are responsible for the company, the market is responsible and responsible for investors.
The former is based on the company's good operating performance, while the latter requires listed companies and their controlling shareholders to have high quality.
For the capital market, this is the core basic elements.
The repurchase of shares by listed companies is conducive to boosting investor confidence and supporting the stock prices of listed companies.
According to the Oriental Securities Research Report, according to the estimated number of shares repurchased by the A-share listed companies as a whole since the beginning of this year, as well as the average price of repurchased shares, the incremental funds brought by the repurchase of shares for the A-share market this year are expected to exceed 150 billion yuan.
In nearly two months, the restoration of the large-scale mural "Tianjin Tin Hau Temple" of the national key cultural protection unit was announced on the 26th, and it will be reopened to the outside world during the National Day this year.
The Tin Hauss map is a large-scale traditional mural that comprehensively reflects the life of the mother.
With the approval of the relevant state departments, it was drawn by Cai Changkui, the former director of Tianjin Folk Museum (Tianggu Palace), from 1991 to 1994.
It is understood that this mural was painted on the south and north palace walls of the main hall of the Tin Hau Palace, with a total length of 32 meters and a height of 2.6 meters, divided into two parts, more than 30 stories such as birth and landing, crossing the sea, and feathering ascension, 358 characters reproduce the life and deeds of Mazu.
Cai Changkui said that in recent years, Tianjin summer rain, winter dry, this "wet and dry" led to the mural crack, rupture part accounted for 60% of the entire mural area.
In order to protect and save the murals of the Mazu deeds, the ancient culture street management committee and the Tin Hau Palace in Nankai District of Tianjin City have launched the restoration project of the Tiangong Temple and the murals in the temple.
The restoration project was led by Cai Changkui, and four famous Chinese painters were invited to participate.
The restoration work is based on the principle of "repairing the old as old", and at the same time, the original murals have been adjusted for local content, and the original places where the murals have been not perfect have been repaired.
In the restoration, we have also made innovations and attempts in color, materials, pen and ink and so on.
After the restoration, the original mural style, spirituality, spirit and artistic style were maintained.
Tiangong Palace was built in 1326, formerly known as the Palace of the Lady, after many renovations, is the oldest building complex in Tianjin, and is one of the earliest Mazu temples in China.
On September 25, the opening ceremony of Beijing Daxing International Airport was held.
The shape of the terminal building of Beijing Daxing International Airport means "Phoenix spreads its wings" and is known as the "seven wonders of the new world".
At present, Beijing Capital International Airport is already overloaded, carrying 100 million+ passengers last year, becoming the second airport in the world with an annual passenger throughput of more than 100 million after the Atlanta airport in the United States.
It is estimated that by 2022, the passenger throughput of Beijing Daxing International Airport will reach 45 million passengers, accounting for 20% of international flights; by 2025, the passenger throughput will reach 72 million passengers, and the proportion of international flights is expected to reach 30%.
As the "new door", how cool is it?
Beijing Daxing International Airport is located between Beijing Daxing District and Guangyang District of Langfang City, Hebei Province, with a straight line distance of 46 kilometers from Tiananmen Square, and is currently the largest new airport under construction in the world.
The floor projection area of the roof cover steel structure of the terminal building reaches 180,000 square meters, with 25 standard football fields in the size of 25 standard football fields.
Beijing Daxing International Airport is the world's first terminal with two arrivals and two departure levels - F1-F4 is international arrival, domestic arrival, domestic departure, international departure.
The double-decker bridge connecting the high-speed and the airport outside the terminal corresponds to the terminal F3 and F4, respectively, the international departure level, and the domestic departure can be two floors.
The first flight of Beijing Daxing International Airport opened the era of Beijing's "double airport".
The new airport is positioned as a large international aviation hub, a new power source for the development of the country, and a regional integrated transportation hub supporting the construction of Xiong'an New Area, as of now, a total of 66 airlines are interested in settling in Beijing Daxing International Airport, of which 20 domestic airlines, 46 Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan regional and foreign airlines, airlines have been approved.
In the winter and spring of 2019, Beijing Daxing International Airport is expected to open 116 routes, including 101 domestic routes and 15 international routes; covering 112 destinations around the world, including 97 domestic destinations and 15 international destinations.
This with Beijing Capital International Airport to form a coordinated development, moderate competition, with international first-class competitiveness of the "double hub" airport pattern, not only ease the capital airport capacity saturation operating pressure, but also better meet the urgent needs of Beijing and surrounding areas of air transport rapid growth, effectively enhance the international competitiveness of China's civil aviation industry.
In order to ensure efficiency and quality, Beijing Daxing International Airport fully considers the geographical location, the airport and the surrounding airspace and operating environment, the airport runway for the first time in the country to adopt the "all-oriented" layout, the use of the world's largest air traffic control automation system, the establishment of China's largest terminal control area, can maximize the efficiency of aviation operation.
For the first time, domestic airports of this scale use localized baggage automatic processing and information management systems, using innovative baggage transfer modes to improve the efficiency of baggage system processing.
The first flight of Beijing Daxing International Airport indicates that the phoenix has spread its wings and cool take off.
This has created more than 40 international and domestic first airports, with a localization rate of more than 98%, which will have a direct and indirect economic impact on the industries in the surrounding areas and inject vitality into Beijing's economic development.
