On September 26, local time, State Councilor and Foreign Minister Wang Yi presided over the Foreign Ministers' Meeting of China and the African Member States of the Security Council at the United Nations Headquarters in New York.
Foreign Minister Tano of Côte d'Ivoire, Foreign Minister of Equatorial Guinea Oyono, South African Foreign Minister Pandor and Foreign Minister Kara of Niger, and Tunisian Foreign Minister Jesinavi attended the meeting.
Wang Yi put forward four suggestions on strengthening cooperation between China and Africa in the Security Council.
First, by uniting strength.
The biggest challenge in the current international situation is unilateralism, the direct consequence of which is that the basic norms governing international relations are being challenged and the role of the United Nations is being undermined, which harms the interests of the vast number of developing countries and small and medium-sized countries, including African countries.
To meet this challenge, it is necessary for China and Africa to be hand in hand and shoulder to shoulder, so that unity can only be strong.
In the Security Council, the three African countries speak with one voice, focusing not just on three votes, but on the entire African continent.
Standing with China and Africa is not just four votes, but will lead other countries to follow suit, influence and shape the agenda of the Security Council.
Since 2018, China and the African members of the Security Council have established a "3+1" coordination mechanism, which should be fully utilized.
Second, solve the dispute through consultation.
China has always advocated the political settlement of hotspot issues, and Africa has a good tradition of consultation and the experience of successful mediation by African regional and subregional organizations.
Many of the complex problems on the Council's agenda, particularly in Africa, have been largely the root causes of colonialism, and some are directly related to external factors.
We must make good use of Chapter VI of the Charter of the United Nations and give full play to the role of the United Nations in good offices and mediation.
Third, self-reliance.
African countries and people know Africa's problems best, and Africa has the ability and wisdom to solve their own problems.
When dealing with hot-spot issues in Africa, the Security Council should focus on listening to and respecting the will of Africa, should play the role of regional and subregional organizations, and should encourage and support endogenous solutions from Africa.
China is willing to strengthen coordination with the African side and firmly promote capacity-building for Africa's autonomous peace operations.
Fourth, it is fundamental to develop.
China and the vast majority of African countries are developing countries, and we must put economic and social development first and support each other's development path.
China is willing to closely align the Belt and Road Initiative with the African Union's Agenda 2063, the United Nations 2030 Agenda for Sustainable Development and the development strategies of African countries, so as to help African countries enhance their development capabilities and eliminate the root causes of conflict.
We must jointly promote the United Nations to increase its investment in Africa's development.
The Ebola outbreak in the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC) has made and will continue to make every effort to provide human and material assistance to the best of its ability, and is willing to coordinate actions with African countries, mobilize the United Nations, WHO and other countries to increase assistance, and give full play to the role of the United Nations Stabilization Mission in the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC).
The neonatal department and other relays to save small lives.
The thrill!
Two-child pregnant mother in advance, on the way to the hospital, a 32-week premature baby can't wait to be born on his father's car.
Fortunately, obstetricians and neonatologists dealt with it in time, and the relay saved this small life.
Coincidentally, on the 19th, 20th and 21st, the obstetrics and neonatal department of Hubei Provincial Maternal and Child Health Hospital received three premature babies born on the road for three consecutive days, the other two were born in 120 emergency vehicles, all 29 weeks of premature babies.
Ms. Cheng is a second-born mother, September 19 at 7 a.m., she felt a little pain in her stomach, thinking that she was 32 weeks pregnant, and the first baby was premature, she packed up the items to be given to give birth, ready to take a bath directly to the hospital.
After 9:30, Ms. Cheng packed up and let her husband drive from Xu Dong's home to the hospital.
Unexpectedly, the car had just opened the door, and the baby could not wait to be born on his father's car co-pilot.
After 20 minutes, Ms. Cheng and the baby finally arrived at the Obstetrics and Gynaecology Building of Hubei Provincial Maternal and Child Health Hospital.
The hospital security guard saw the panicked couple and the baby, immediately notified the obstetric delivery room, deputy chief physician Zhang Huan and other four doctors and midwife Liu Yanyan rushed downstairs with the delivery bag and umbilical cord plate.
"At that time, the mother half lying on the car co-pilot, under the amniotic fluid and blood, a baby boy is next to, but also connected to the umbilical cord."
Zhang Huan asked to know that the baby is a 32-week premature baby, parents on the road did not have time to cover the child, early autumn morning has a cool, he froze pale skin, no crying, limbs slumped.
Liu Yanyan rushed to the co-pilot to treat the baby umbilical cord, Zhang Huan from the cab into, quickly opened the delivery bag, with the inside of the treatment towel and the bag of the bag to pack a few layers of warmth for the child, and to the newborn to clean up the respiratory tract (pictured), and then holding the baby to the 12th floor neonatology.
After the neonatal medical doctor learned the news, he immediately rushed to the nurse's station to rescue the premature baby.
At that time, the baby's face was purple, there was a lack of oxygen, the doctor immediately gave him a tracheal intubation, less than a minute, the baby regained his heartbeat, the skin color gradually restored rosy, and the recovery was successful.
After admission to the hospital, the 32-week-old baby was on a ventilator, continued to rescue, breathing smoothly, and successfully withdrew the next day.
After a week of treatment, the baby's vital signs are stable, breathing is smooth, and a small amount of breastfeeding has begun.
Coincidentally, on the 19th, 20th and 21st, the obstetrics and neonatology department of the hospital received three premature babies born on the road for three consecutive days, the other two were born in 120 emergency vehicles, all 29 weeks of premature babies, and are currently actively treated in the neonatology department.
Sun Guoqiang, head of obstetrics at the Provincial Maternal and Child Health Hospital, said that in recent years, the province's mothers and children have treated many babies born on the subway and in private cars, and bad treatment may threaten the life and safety of the mother and child.
Director Sun reminded that once a pregnant mother has abdominal pain, broken water, see red and other phenomena, she should immediately come to the hospital for treatment.
If you are at home or on the road, the mother should be as flat as possible, you can put a blanket under your hips to prevent the baby from hitting the ground after delivery, and the child should be warm immediately after delivery, and be sent to the doctor as soon as possible.
