Research shows that manufacturing has become the focus of major countries in the world.
Hefei, September 27 (Xinhua) -- A few days ago, the National Intellectual Property Operation Public Service Platform released the "Global Manufacturing Innovation Index White Paper" in Hefei, Anhui Province.
The white paper shows that the manufacturing industry has become the focus of major countries in the world.
This is the reporter's understanding at the "2019 World Manufacturing Conference Intellectual Property Operation and Protection Forum" held in Hefei.
Focusing on intellectual property rights to help China's manufacturing upgrade, from the macro level of policy interpretation and the micro perspective of enterprise practice, the forum comprehensively explores the innovative measures of intellectual property operation and protection in the manufacturing industry, in-depth discussion on the hot topic of intellectual property protection in the manufacturing industry, continuously improve the ability to use intellectual property rights in high quality, and accelerate the construction of the intelligent upgrade advantages of the manufacturing industry.
The forum invited the State Intellectual Property Office, scholars from the Chinese Academy of Sciences, as well as experts from relevant domestic and foreign industry organizations and professional research institutions to share experiences and contribute ideas on how to strengthen intellectual property protection and promote the use of intellectual property rights.
At the forum, the Anhui Provincial Market Supervision and Administration Bureau issued the "Patent Navigation Anhui Innovation Development Quality Analysis and Evaluation" report, according to the results of the patent navigation regional innovation high-quality development index, Anhui Province in 2018 patent navigation regional innovation high-quality development index ranked eighth in the country's 31 provinces, districts and cities, and the innovation factor agglomeration index ranked fourth in the country.
The forum was hosted by the People's Government of Anhui Province and jointly hosted by the Anhui Provincial Market Supervision Administration, the National Intellectual Property Operation Public Service Platform and the China Intellectual Property Development Alliance.
