After Shanghai, Beijing has become the second city in China with two airports, and Shanghai Hongqiao International Airport mainly serves domestic aviation affairs, Pudong Airport is similar to international shipping and aviation, and the future capital airport and Daxing Airport will also serve the differentiated positioning of domestic and international aviation business, providing more segmented services.
Daxing Airport, from the perspective of business development, is more of a positive impact on the capital airport.
Capital Airport's passenger throughput exceeded 100 million in 2018, ranking first in the country, but compared with the fast-growing business demand, there is still a significant difference in capacity, especially the demand for international routes.
In order to better serve the needs of domestic and foreign passengers for travel and travel, and to adapt to the urban development trend of Beijing's increasingly open and international standards, Daxing International Airport is positioned as a large-scale international hub airport, and plans to meet the annual passenger throughput of 100 million passengers and 4 million tons of cargo and mail throughput in the future.
Therefore, the two airports do not overlap, respectively, for different customer groups, also have enough market space.
From the economic accounting point of view, the opening of Daxing International Airport will obviously form a win-win effect, alleviate the tension of Beijing Airlines, accelerate the growth rate of passenger and cargo throughput, and create an incremental cake for the dual nuclear operation of Capital Airlines.
From the user's point of view, with the opening of Daxing International Airport, it is not necessary to focus on the capital airport in the future, but also to reduce a series of problems caused by the excessive concentration of routes, such as the longer the security time of the station, the slow boarding speed of passengers, indirectly increase the time of the aircraft and passengers at the airport, increase the burden of airport operation, and reduce the burden of shipping through the capital airport, in fact, it also improves the travel experience of passengers.
