The deepest railway in our country has been dug into the main well.
Xinhua News Agency, Kunming, September 27 (Reporter Ding Yiquan) According to the China Railway Tunnel Bureau Group Co., Ltd., the first long tunnel of China's railway - Da (Li) Rui (Li) Railway Gaoligongshan Tunnel No. 1 shaft successfully dug into the end, the well depth of 762.59 meters broke the deepest record of domestic railway shaft.
In the construction of the tunnel, the shaft can play a role in improving tunnel ventilation, improving the efficiency of the rut, and ensuring the safety of the construction.
Song Tao, chief engineer of the Dangjing Industrial Zone of the China Railway Tunnel Bureau, said: "After the successful excavation of the main well of the No. 1 shaft of the Gaoligongshan Tunnel, it will help to promote the construction of the bottom of the well, open a number of work surfaces for the later construction of the main well, and speed up the construction progress of the entire Gaoligongshan Tunnel."
Song Tao introduced that the construction of the silo No. 1 of Gaoligongshan Tunnel adopts the chirping method, equipped with the well-scuttering well frame, chising and swelling crane, the overall mobile metal template, the FJD-6A type umbrella drill, the center rotary rock machine and other large-scale specialized machinery, forming a mechanized excavation system, out-crowding system, suspension system, hushing system, shaved lift system, etc.The whole process of mechanized operations such as pouring has greatly accelerated the construction progress.
It is understood that the Darui Railway from Dali to the west to Ruili, the total length of about 331 kilometers, the design speed of 140 kilometers per hour, is an important part of the China-Myanmar international railway channel.
Gaoligong Mountain Tunnel is 34.538 kilometers long, which is the first long tunnel of China's railway.
