China's deepest record for railway tunnel shafts has been set
China-Singapore Social Security Mountain September 27th (Zhang Weiming Xu Zhou Jingbo) After more than 1200 days of day and night construction, in the construction of the University (Li) Rui (Li) Railway Gaoligongshan Tunnel No. 1 shaft completed excavation on the 27th, the well depth reached 762.59 meters below the ground, breaking the record of the deepest shaft in China's railway tunnel, and this record was created in a large number of water surges.
The 34.5-kilometer-long Darui Railway Gaoligong Mountain Tunnel is located in Yunnan, and the tunnel runs through the Gaoligong Mountain Mountains from the west bank of the Fury River, and is the longest tunnel in Asia.
The tunnel passes through 19 fracture zones and is buried at a maximum depth of 1,155 meters, as it covers almost all the bad geology and major risks that may be encountered in tunnel construction, and the Gaoligongshan Tunnel is known as the "geological museum" of tunnel construction.
The shaft is the most important auxiliary tunnel of the Gaoligong Mountain Tunnel, and it is shouldering the important task of increasing the working surface to achieve "long tunnel short play" and the ventilation of railway operation in the later period.
The first shaft was successfully dug to the bottom of the well, marking the Gaoligongshan Tunnel officially entered the horizontal tunnel construction, and after the excavation and equipment replacement of the bottom of the well yard, the underground can increase 4 working surfaces to speed up the excavation speed of the tunnel.
"The shaft is all in the granite formation, because the granite formation cracks more, can not stop the water, from the top to the bottom of the flow, basically how deep the well how much deep water pressure."
China Railway Tunnel Bureau Da Rui Railway Project Department chief engineer Shi Jingzhao told reporters that in the construction of the shaft, there have been many times in the danger of sudden mud surge, collapse, etc. The construction party invited experts to put the pulse on the spot, more than 20 times to discuss the treatment plan.
"The maximum water surge in the shaft, up to more than 300 cubic meters per hour, more than 700 meters deep at the bottom of the well, the water pressure is equivalent to 700 meters deep seabed."
"If you don't pump and drain in time, it will flood the well 10 meters in an hour, we are almost 85% of the time for water treatment, and 15% of the time is spent digging."
In order to overcome the geological problems such as longitudinal development, sudden mud surge water, and water-rich granite, the tunnel construction adopts systematic water treatment measures combined with "exploration, injection and excavation" to reduce the construction risk.
After many improvements, the construction of the No. 1 shaft has formed a mechanized pipeline such as excavation system, rut system, suspension system, and winch lifting system, which has realized the whole process of mechanized operations such as eye-catching, blasting, out-of-cell, template installation, and concrete pouring, and accelerated the construction progress.
Finally, after more than 1,200 days of day and night construction, the shaft successfully completed the excavation at a depth of 762.59 meters.
