Starting next year, Chinese students can apply for German undergraduates with college entrance examination results.
Recently, the Anabin database responsible for the evaluation and certification of foreign academic qualifications in Germany announced on the official website: starting in 2020, China's high school graduates can apply directly to German universities with college entrance examination results, do not need to register in domestic universities.
Prior to this, Chinese high school graduates who want to apply to German universities need to study for one semester (211,985 universities) or three semesters (general undergraduate) in China, and pass the APS audit or TestAS exam.
The release of the new rules may save at least half a year for Chinese students who are willing to study in Germany.
It is reported that the new regulations will come into effect in the second half of 2019.
Applicants must meet: complete 12 years of formal compulsory education, get a high school diploma; participate in the entrance examination, college entrance examination, and college entrance examination score of 70% or above (if the total score of 750 points, you need to reach more than 525 points), and including two language scores and a mathematics or natural science score.
In addition, the specific professional requirements for college entrance examination results are not the same.
For example, to apply for medical science, oral medicine, veterinary science, pharmacy and other majors, the college entrance examination score must reach 80% of the full score, and the college entrance examination subjects must include at least two in mathematics, physics, chemistry, biology, or participate in the integration; apply to the legal major, college entrance examination score must reach a full score of 80%, and college entrance examination subjects must include foreign language, history, geography at least two, or participate in the text.
According to incomplete statistics, many countries, including Germany, the United Kingdom, Canada, Australia, etc., have recognized China's college entrance examination results.
In the United Kingdom, for example, universities such as the University of Cambridge, the University of Birmingham, and the University of Leicester all accept Chinese students to apply for college entrance examination results.
