State Council Information Office Releases White Paper on China and the World in the New Era
On the occasion of the 70th anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of China, the Information Office of the State Council issued a white paper on China and the world in the
Xu Lin, Vice Minister of the Central Propaganda Department and Director of the Information Office of the State Council, said that the white paper systematically introduces China's development achievements, development path and development trend, and explains China's relations with the world in depth on issues such as "where China comes from and where it is going", "what kind of world China promotes construction" and "how China develops to get along with the world", so as to enhance the international community's understanding and understanding of China's development.
The white paper pointed out that in the past 70 years, under the leadership of the Communist Party of China, China has undergone tremendous changes and created a development miracle unprecedented in human history, especially since the 18th National Congress of the Communist Party of China, China's development has made historic achievements and undergone historic changes.
Through a large amount of data and facts, the white paper introduces the great achievements, significance and world contributions of China's development in the past 70 years.
The white paper pointed out that China has completed the development process of developed countries for hundreds of years in a few decades, the total economy has jumped to the second place in the world, and nearly 1.4 billion people have got rid of the material shortage, generally reached a well-off level, and enjoyed unprecedented dignity and rights.
The white paper emphasizes that in the past 70 years, the Chinese people have made self-made, self-reliant and hard-working, and created a new world; in the past 70 years, China has developed in the relationship and interaction with the world, embraced the world, studied the world, and contributed to the world; in the past 70 years, while realizing self-development, China has contributed to world peace and injected impetus into the common development of all countries.
The fundamental reason for the success of China's development in the past 70 years is that under the leadership of the Communist Party of China, the Chinese people have found the correct development path of socialism with Chinese characteristics and followed this path unswervingly.
The white paper emphasizes that the path of socialism with Chinese characteristics is a road established from the perspective of national conditions, a road that puts the interests of the people first, a road of reform and innovation, a road for seeking common development in opening up, and a road of the country in accordance with the rule of law in an all-round way.
This development path of China, which is in line with China's national conditions and meets the requirements of the times, will show brighter development prospects with the advancement of the times.
In response to the international community's concern about China's development, the white paper emphasizes that the realization of the country's prosperity and strength, national rejuvenation and people's happiness is both the dream of the Chinese people and the common dream of the people of all countries.
The white paper pointed out that China is the main stabilizer and power source of world economic growth, all-round opening up to create more opportunities for the development of all countries, China provides more public goods for the international community, China's development provides experience and reference for other developing countries, and China will never take the road of "national strength must dominate".
In the face of the question of what happened to the world and what to do with mankind, the white paper pointed out that the world is in a century of great changes, and human society is both full of hope and full of challenges.
China has put forward the building of a community with a shared future for mankind, opened up a new path of development with win-win cooperation and common construction and sharing, and provided new choices for human development.
The white paper calls on all countries to unite to build a new type of international relations, promote new-type economic globalization, safeguard the international system with the United Nations as the core, promote exchanges and mutual learning among civilizations, and jointly promote the construction of a community with a shared future for mankind and a better world.
With the increasing development of China, the international community is generally concerned about how the developed China can get along with the world.
The white paper pointed out that China's development cannot be separated from the world, and the world's peaceful development, prosperity and stability cannot be separated from China.
China has always put its own development in the coordinate system of human development, adhered to win-win cooperation and common development, adhered to maintaining and promoting economic globalization, actively developed global partnerships, firmly supported multilateralism, safeguarded international fairness and justice, promoted the high-quality development of the Belt and Road Initiative, actively participated in leading the reform and construction of the global governance system, and always been a builder of world peace, a contributor to global development, and a defender of the international order.
At present, China's development has entered a new era.
The white paper pointed out that in the new era, China's determination to take the road of socialism with Chinese characteristics will not change, the determination of learning from each other and win-win cooperation with other countries will not change, and the determination to walk hand in hand with the world will not change.
The white paper concludes that in today's world, the future and destiny of all countries have never been so closely linked as they are now.
The white paper "China and the World in the New Era" consists of a foreword, text and concluding remarks, with a full text of more than 29,000 words.
The white paper is published in eight languages, including Chinese, English, French, Russian, German, West, A, and Sun, and published by the People's Publishing House and the Foreign Language Publishing House respectively, and distributed in Xinhua bookstores across the country.
