A villager hunted wild animals in Baokang County, Hubei Province, was ordered to "obligate to patrol the mountain"
A villager in Baokang County, Hubei Province, was sentenced for hunting wild animals and ordered to compensate 15,420 yuan (RMB, the same below) for the restoration of ecological resources and environmental damage.
Due to the poverty of the defendant's family, the procuratorial organ activated the cost of ecological restoration of alternative labor compensation, and realized the organic unification of legal and social effects.
Wang Zhongliang, deputy procurator of the Baokang County Procuratorate, introduced on the 27th that through three months of alternative labor such as "obligatory mountain patrol", the defendant Zhou has established a deep feeling with wild macaque monkeys, and deeply blames himself for hunting animals before.
On June 21 this year, a criminal incidental civil public interest lawsuit in the field of ecological resources filed by the Baokang County Procuratorate was publicly heard in the county court and pronounced in court.
The defendant Zhou was sentenced to three years in prison, suspended for four years, and fined 3,000 yuan, and ordered to compensate ecological resources and environmental damage repair costs of 15,420 yuan.
After investigation, Zhou began to set up a power grid on the cliffs in late January 2014, and has hunted more than 20 wild animals, including wildebeest, small, and crown deer.
It belongs to the national second-class endangered wild protected animals, and small and crowned deer are listed in the National Terrestrial Wildlife Conservation List.
During the trial, Zhou confessed to his illegal facts and actions, and was willing to bear incidental civil liability.
However, considering the poor economic situation in Zhou's home, under the coordination of the Baokang County Procuratorate, the local village committee, the forest station, and Zhou reached an agreement on the cost of alternative labor compensation for ecological restoration: that is, Zhou has provided public welfare services to offset the ecological restoration costs by carrying out macaque monkey domestication and care work in the village macaque protection area, compulsory mountain patrol and forest protection for one year.
For the prosecutor's recommendation, the court agreed to Zhou's execution of probation and actively fulfilled the obligation of "alternative labor compensation for ecological restoration costs".
At present, Zhou has been working in the macaque protection area for 3 months, and has been actively patrolling the mountain and performing well.
In recent years, the Baokang County Procuratorate has organically integrated procuratorial functions and social governance behaviors in practice, scientifically used procuratorial recommendations, investigation supervision, litigation supervision and other supervision methods, and used judicial means to minimize the damage caused by criminal acts to the ecological environment.
