Economic and trade frictions affect the "report card" of the US economy.
The U.S. economic "report card" for the second quarter of this year showed that the growth rate of U.S. gross domestic product (GDP) slowed down significantly compared with the previous quarter, driven by a sharp decline in private-sector investment and exports.
Analysts pointed out that economic and trade frictions and the uncertainty they bring are the main reasons for the decline in private sector investment and exports in the second quarter.
The final revised data released by the US Department of Commerce on the 26th shows that the US GDP increased by 2% year-on-year in the second quarter, which is the same as the revised data previously released, but significantly lower than the 3.1% in the first quarter.
The data shows that consumption growth has become the main factor supporting the US economic growth in the second quarter.
Personal consumption expenditure, which accounts for about 70% of the total US economy, increased by 4.6% month-on-quarter, boosting economic growth by 3.03 percentage points.
In addition, government consumption expenditure and investment boosted economic growth by 0.82 percentage points.
However, private sector investment in the second quarter fell by 6.3% from the previous quarter, dragging down 1.16 percentage points of economic growth in the quarter; exports fell by 5.7% from the previous quarter, and net exports dragged down the economic growth of 0.68 percentage points in the quarter.
Barry Knapp, managing partner of Eindez macroeconomic consulting firm in the United States, said that private sector investment not only failed to maintain the momentum of growth last year, but fell sharply, because economic and trade frictions and rising uncertainty hit business confidence.
Knapp believes that under the influence of policy uncertainty, US corporate capital expenditure is expected to remain in a downward trend next year.
Analysts believe that although consumption growth has formed a strong support for the US economy in the second quarter, there are more and more signs that economic and trade frictions and the uncertainty it brings have affected consumer confidence and adversely affected the US consumption outlook.
Richard Curtin, a professor of economics at the University of Michigan and the head of the survey, said that in the most recent survey, 38% of consumers spontaneously mentioned the negative impact of tariffs on the US economy, which is a new high in a year and a half.
For the future trend of the US economy, analysts generally believe that the US economy will continue to slow down.
But some experts said that if the economic and trade frictions are eased, the performance of the US industrial sector and financial markets will improve.
Karin Birch, a global economist at the British Economist Intelligence Unit, expects that the future US economy will continue its gradual downward trend since this year, and the growth rate will fall to a lower level than in the second quarter.
Mark Zandi, chief economist at Moody's Analytics, predicts that under the premise that economic and trade frictions will not continue to escalate, the US economy will grow by 2.3% this year and further slow to 1.6% next year.
Ellen Hatzen, investment manager of Putnam Investment Company, pointed out that the biggest concern of the current business is the economic and trade dispute and the uncertainty it brings, if the economic and trade disputes can be resolved, the uncertainty will be greatly reduced, and the performance of the industrial sector will be much better than now.
Matt Meley, equity strategist at Miller-Tabak Asset Management, said that economic and trade frictions are still the "first problem" and the main cause of the sharp fluctuations in the US capital market this year. Whether economic and trade frictions can be properly resolved will be the key to the direction of the US capital market in the rest of this year.
Ningxia's first joint parental leave for parents of children aged 0 to 3 years can take 10 days a year
Protecting women's legitimate rights and interests is the embodiment of respecting and protecting human rights, and it is also an important symbol of the progress of social civilization.
On September 27, at the 15th meeting of the Standing Committee of the 12th National People's Congress of Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region, the Regulations on the Protection of Women's Rights and Interests of Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region were passed with high votes.
This is the first provincial-level formulation and promulgation of a comprehensive system to safeguard the legitimate rights and interests of women's local regulations, which will be formally implemented on November 1, 2019.
It is understood that the "Regulations" adopted this time are revised on the basis of the implementation of the "Measures for the Protection of the Rights and Interests of Women in Ningxia" in 2007, which are divided into 9 chapters and 65 articles, including general principles, political rights, cultural and educational rights and interests, labor and social security rights and interests, property rights and interests, personal rights, marriage and family rights, legal responsibilities, and by-laws.
In the Regulations, Ningxia encourages the exploration and implementation of joint parental leave for couples, which is still the first in the country.
In April this year, the "Guiding Opinions on Promoting the Development of Care Services for Infants and Young Children Under 3" issued by the General Office of the State Council has a relevant description of the common parenting of husband and wife.
In the process of revising the Regulations, Ningxia proposed to "encourage employers to give joint parental leave to couples who have children in accordance with laws and regulations, and each year between the child's zero to three years of age and ten days of common parental leave each year."
At the same time, the Ordinance highlights the anti-sexual harassment and the protection of female minors.
Article 43 of the Regulations incorporates the latest legislative achievements in China's current civil code personality rights, and details the constituent elements of sexual harassment, the main body and mechanism of anti-sexual harassment.
Article 44 of the Ordinance explicitly prohibits the frequent sexual abuse of girls, and requires educational institutions to carry out relevant education, protection and prevention work, which has become a new benchmark for the protection of girls in local legislation.
Article 35 of the Ordinance clearly stipulates women's rights to information about the common property of the common property and the obligations of property registration agencies and related subjects, and provides solid institutional support for women's rights.
In addition, in response to social hot-spot issues - gender discrimination in employment, Article 26 of the Ordinance not only prohibits direct discrimination, but also prohibits indirect discrimination, and absorbs the latest joint interviews with practical experience, strengthens the punishment for gender discrimination violations, and more effectively safeguards the legitimate rights and interests of women.
In recent years, the Ningxia Women's Federation, together with the Public Inspection and Law Department and the Civil Affairs Department, have promoted and introduced social and professional forces to participate in the mediation of marriage and family conflicts and disputes and anti-domestic violence, with remarkable results.
The Regulations summarize and improve this, and in many laws, encourage the mobilization of social forces and the accumulation of social resources to jointly safeguard the rights and interests of women, and require people's governments at or above the county level to provide stable and institutional guarantees and support through the purchase of services.
