The tax collection helps to bring benefits to public health.
On the evening of September 25, local time, the Chinese Embassy in Canada held a reception in Ottawa to celebrate the 70th anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of China.
OTTAWA, Sept. 26 (Xinhua) -- The new Chinese Ambassador to Canada Cong Peiwu held a reception to celebrate the 70th anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of China in Ottawa on the evening of September 25 local time.
In his speech, Cong Peiwu said that in the 70 years since the founding of New China, under the strong leadership of the Communist Party of China and the joint efforts of the people of the country, the cause of socialism with Chinese characteristics has achieved remarkable achievements, which has not only profoundly changed the face of China and benefited its own people, but also produced far-reaching world significance.
Based on its own national conditions, China has opened up a path of socialism with Chinese characteristics, expanded the way for developing countries to move toward modernization, and contributed Chinese wisdom and Chinese solutions to solve human problems.
The guests stop to watch the theme exhibition of the 70th anniversary of New China held at the same time in the venue.
Cong Peiwu said that China has created a rare miracle in the history of human development in the world and made important contributions to promoting world peace and development.
China adheres to an independent foreign policy of peace, has always advocated the basic norms of international relations with the Five Principles of Peaceful Coexistence as the core, and is a builder of world peace, a contributor to global development, and a defender of the international order.
China's development has provided new opportunities for the development of all countries in the world, including Canada, and benefited the people of all countries.
Cong Peiwu stressed that the development of China-Canada relations in the past 50 years shows that only by upholding the principles of equality and mutual respect can bilateral relations move forward on the right track.
On the contrary, the relationship between the two countries will be frustrated and the interests of the two countries will be damaged.
At present, China-Canada relations have encountered serious difficulties, and the responsibility is not on China.
"The bell must also be tied to the bell man."
It is hoped that the Canadian side will come up with a solution to properly resolve outstanding issues in bilateral relations as soon as possible and create conditions for bilateral relations to return to the right track.
More than 700 Canadian government officials, U.S. senators, friendly people from all walks of life, diplomatic envoys to Canada, and overseas Chinese, Chinese-funded institutions and international students attended the reception.
The Chinese Embassy in Canada, such as Chen Mingjian and the public participation in the filial piety army, attended the reception.
The reception held a themed photo exhibition on the 70th anniversary of the founding of New China, and promotional videos such as "China 2019" and "Beautiful China" were broadcast.
Chinese and Canadian artists and embassy diplomats performed distinctive literary and artistic programs.
This is also the first time that Cong Peiwu, the 16th Chinese ambassador to Canada, has appeared in public activities since his new appearance.
Cong Peiwu arrived in Canada on September 22 and submitted a copy of the letter to the Chief Protocol Officer of Canada and the Director of Protocol of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, Wheeler, in Ottawa the following day.
Born in May 1967, Cong Peiwu graduated from the Diplomatic Academy.
He was stationed at the Chinese Embassy in Canada at the beginning of this century.
Prior to his assignment to Canada, he served as the director of the North American and Oceania Department of the Chinese Ministry of Foreign Affairs, and previously served as the Minister Counsellor and Minister of the Chinese Embassy in the United Kingdom.
