China's development is an opportunity, not a threat and a challenge to the world.
(New China 70 years) White paper: China's development is an opportunity for the world, not a threat and a challenge.
The white paper pointed out that China's development is an opportunity, not a threat and a challenge to the world.
The white paper said that with the rapid improvement of China's comprehensive national strength and international influence, some people in the world are worried that China will take the road of "national power must dominate", and some people put forward the so-called "China threat theory".
This is both a cognitive misreading, a deep-seated bias, a psychological imbalance brought about by the growth of strength, and a deliberate distortion of its vested interests.
The realization of national prosperity, national rejuvenation and people's happiness is both the dream of the Chinese people and the common dream of the people of all countries.
"China's development is an opportunity, not a threat and a challenge to the world."
The white paper pointed out that China is the main stabilizer and power source of world economic growth, China is the largest contributor to world economic growth, China's scientific and technological innovation injects new momentum into world economic growth, and the role of the stabilizer and power source of China's economy in the future is more prominent.
At present, the momentum of world economic growth is insufficient, and a stable Chinese economy is becoming more and more important to the world.
China's economy is shifting from high-speed growth to high-quality development, new industrialization, informatization, urbanization, and agricultural modernization are accelerating, the economic structure is deeply adjusted, industrial optimization continues to be upgraded, and new economic growth points are constantly emerging.
