The white paper emphasizes that China's economy and the world economy have undergone structural changes and are deeply integrated.
China, with a more stable economy, higher quality of growth and promising growth prospects, is a long-term positive for world economic development.
It is neither feasible nor harmful to view China's economic development as a "threat" and a "challenge" to squeeze China out of the global industrial chain, supply chain, and value chain, so that China can "decouple" from the world economy.
The white paper pointed out that all-round opening up creates more opportunities for all countries to share the "China dividend".
China unswervingly pursues a mutually beneficial and win-win opening-up strategy to achieve greater and higher levels of opening-up, China has the world's most potential consumer market, China is the most attractive investment destination, and a larger "going out" to benefit more countries.
“Openness should be two-way and mutually beneficial, not one-way and one-sided benefits.
Mutually beneficial two ways can be long-term lasting.”
The white paper said that China is committed to continuously expand imports, relax market access, improve the business environment, and strengthen intellectual property protection, and other countries should also expand opening up and take corresponding measures to strive to improve their business environment.
Only when all parties meet each other can we create an open, inclusive, inclusive, balanced and win-win development environment, and jointly make the "cake" of development bigger and bigger, and form a mutually beneficial and win-win community of interests.
The white paper pointed out that China provides more public goods to the international community.
This includes promoting high-quality co-construction of the Belt and Road Initiative, building a platform for multilateral dialogue and cooperation, actively participating in international and regional affairs, and actively carrying out foreign assistance.
"China's development has benefited from the international community, and it has never forgotten to give back to the international community to provide more and better public goods for the international community."
