"One turn has been" two major UHV projects put into operation
On the 26th, the ±1100 kV high-voltage direct current transmission project from the east to the south and the Sutong 1000 kV AC UHV GIL comprehensive pipe corridor project were put into operation.
These two projects occupy the commanding heights of the current world transmission technology in their respective fields, and after commissioning, China's energy optimization will be greatly improved.
Guo Zhi, chief economist of the National Energy Board, said that the project from the east to the south is the world's largest power transmission capacity and the farthest transmission distance.
Its operation is of great significance to promote the development of Xinjiang's energy base and ensure the power supply in East China.
GIL, that is, gas-insulated metal closed transmission lines.
Sutong pipe corridor project has created a record of the highest voltage level and the strongest conveying capacity in the world of the GIL project, and realized the operation of the 'AC double loop' of the highest voltage level of the East China backbone grid.
According to the State Grid Corporation, the transmission distance from the quasi-east to the south project is as long as 3,324 kilometers.
If conventional technology is used, more than 15% of the electricity will be lost on the way, and the project has been researched and developed, greatly increasing the economic transmission distance to more than 3,000 kilometers.
After the project is put into operation, it can deliver 100 million degrees of electricity every 8 hours and 20 minutes, which can help solve the problem of the consumption of existing new energy in Xinjiang.
According to the full load estimate, the annual power transmission of this single line will reach 60 to 85 billion kWh, which can meet more than half of Shanghai's electricity consumption in the whole year.
Sutong GIL integrated corridor project is a control project of the UHV AC ring network across the Yangtze River.
If you use a conventional overhead line across the river, you need to build two giant towers with more than 450 meters on the Yangtze River, and build an artificial island of more than four football fields for each tower.
In this regard, the national grid bold innovation, the development of compact UHV AC GIL transmission technology, through the tunnel from the water across the river, to avoid the impact on the golden channel.
The two projects have promoted China's electrical equipment manufacturing capacity to achieve a new leap.
At present, the national power grid has built a total of "10 to 11 straight" UHV project, and "4 to 3 straight" is under construction.
