The reporter learned from the Yunnan Provincial Academy of Agricultural Sciences on the 27th that at present, the Yunnan grassland nocturnal moth has been effectively prevented and controlled, which has not caused a large-scale outbreak and disaster, and the prevention and control work has achieved phased results.
In January this year, Jiangcheng County, Pu'er City, Yunnan Province, first discovered the grassland nocturnal moth that moved in from abroad, and then confirmed it in 129 counties in Yunnan, and the grass-grass nocturnal moth also spread from Yunnan to mainland China, posing a direct threat to China's food production.
Grassland nocturnal moth is a multi-eating long-distance migratory important agricultural pest originating in the tropical and subtropical regions of the Americas, and is a major migratory pest of the United Nations Food and Agriculture Organization (FAO) global warning, with "international, migratory, explosive and destructive" characteristics.
The pest endangers more than 80 kinds of crops such as corn, sugarcane, and sorghum, and has a large amount of food intake, which can cause up to 70% of the yield loss.
Prevention and control is difficult, and there is no registered pesticide for the prevention and control of the worm in China.
Since the grassland nocturnal moth moved and flew into Yunnan, the Yunnan Provincial Academy of Agricultural Sciences has selected researchers from Aidong to lead the innovation team of the Yunnan Provincial Academy of Agricultural Sciences in coordination with the Green Prevention and Control Province, and went to the front line to investigate, collect samples, and carry out technical guidance and test demonstrations.
The team has initially grasped the population characteristics of Yunnan grassland nocturnal moths, natural enemy insect resources, overseas insect source characteristics, population relocation trajectory, drug virulence and field control effect.
They actively carry out research and application of green prevention and control technology, through the implementation of new green prevention and control technologies such as population monitoring, adult dders, scientific drugs and agronomic measures, the prevention and control effect in the demonstration area has reached more than 90%, while reducing the use of chemical pesticides, protecting the natural enemy resources and ecological environment, and providing technical protection for the outbreak and sustainable management of grassland nocturnal moths in Yunnan.
At present, the Yunnan grassland nocturnal moth has been effectively prevented and controlled, which has not caused a large-scale outbreak, and the prevention and control work has achieved phased results.
In the next step, the Yunnan Provincial Academy of Agricultural Sciences will focus on the ecological mechanism of population relocation and invasion, and break through the construction of biological prevention and green prevention and control technology system.
At the same time, we will actively promote cross-border international cooperation, and strive to establish joint key laboratories and joint monitoring outlets and demonstration zones overseas, so as to enhance the all-round monitoring and early warning capabilities of Yunnan grassland night moths.
