The 86th China-Laos Myanmar-Thailand-Mekong River joint patrol law enforcement was completed.
The reporter learned from the press office of the Yunnan Provincial Public Security Department on the 27th that at 15:30 on the same day, three Chinese law enforcement boats and two law enforcement boats from China and Laos participating in the 86th China-Laos Myanmar-Thailand Mekong River joint patrol and law enforcement successfully berthed in China's port, marking the successful conclusion of the joint patrol law enforcement operation.
The operation was launched on the 24th in Guanxiang, which lasted 4 days and 3 nights, and a total of 136 law enforcement personnel and 6 law enforcement boats were sent by the four countries of Myanmar and Thailand.
During the operation, the formation carried out joint patrols, anti-drug propaganda and other activities in key waters such as the Golden Triangle, the Lao Ban Xianguo and Mengmo.
In addition, the Chinese side also sent a team of police combat instructors to the Lao People's Army 122 and 133 border troops to carry out practical police combat skills exchange, effectively improving the emergency response ability of law enforcement personnel of the two sides to jointly deal with emergencies.
The four countries also held a law enforcement cooperation and exchange meeting in Qingsheng, Thailand, to inform each other about the recent situation of various countries in border management, combating drug crimes and the security situation in the Mekong River Basin, and reached consensus on strengthening information exchange, research and judgment and law enforcement cooperation; and held four-country cultural and sports exchange activities to carry out competitions such as football, rattan ball, iron ball and tug-of-war, effectively enhance mutual understanding between law enforcement officers and the four-country law enforcement cooperation and friendship.
