The new regulations for soliciting opinions: social capital needs to be qualified to obtain rural land management rights
Social capital to obtain rural land management rights need to be qualified
Measures for the Administration of the Transfer of Rural Land Management Rights for Public Comment Proposed Supervision of the Transfer of Social Capital Transfers of Industrial and Commercial Enterprises to Obtain Land Management Rights
Yesterday, the website of the Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Affairs issued a notice on the "Administrative Measures for the Transfer of Rural Land Management Rights (Revised Draft)" (hereinafter referred to as the "Draft for Comment"), which increased the supervision and risk prevention of social capital transfer to obtain land management rights by industrial and commercial enterprises.
The draft opinion is now open to public consultation.
According to the Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Affairs, in order to implement the newly revised Law on Rural Land Contracting, further consolidate and improve the basic rural management system, deepen the reform of the rural land system, and implement the "separation of powers" system, the Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Affairs has revised the Measures for the Administration of the Transfer of Rural Land Contractual Management Rights and formed the "Draft Opinions".
Beijing Youth Daily reporter learned that the first release of the "Draft of Opinions" has many important changes.
The newly revised "Rural Land Contracting Law" clarifies the scope of land transfer, implements the concept of "separating the three rights", and sets up "land contract management right" and "land management right" respectively, making a clear distinction between the transfer of land contract management rights, swapping and the transfer of land management rights (leasing, subcontracting, equity or other means).
In the "Draft of Opinions", in order to implement the concept of "sequence separation of powers", effectively respond to the "rural land contracting law" amendment to the main thrust of the law, and take into account the large differences between the transfer of land management rights and the exchange of land contract management rights, transfer in the parties, procedures, supervision and other aspects, this revised draft defines the scope of transfer, focuses on the transfer of land management rights, including leasing, shareholding, etc., and revises the name of the regulations from the "Rural land management management rights management management approach".
The transfer and exchange of land contractual management rights will be stipulated in separate management measures.
The "Draft Opinion" pointed out that in the context of the "separation of powers", farmers only have the right to land management for a certain period of time.
In theory, even in the event of bankruptcy liquidation, farmers only have the risk of losing the right to operate for a certain period of time, so it is no longer necessary to provide for the return of the original contractor to the original contractor, and there is a conflict with the Bankruptcy Law.
In response to the problem of preventing farmers' land loss risks, in practice, preferred stocks, rent stocks first, buybacks and other methods have been produced.
Considering that preferred stocks have a more mature theoretical discussion in the company law, it is recommended to use them as an advocacy provision to prevent the risk of loss of equity.
